ers Requirements</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Children must be 7 years of age on or before 30 September in the year of application for their memberships to be accepted. Children under the age of 13 must join with at least one parent/guardian. Teens up to age 18 who are participating in Surf Sport must join with parent(s) as well.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>All members between the age of 13 and 30 years( who are not parents of Nippers) are required to participate in 16 hours of compulsory patrol per session.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Senior Carnival Competitors and Patrollers (13+) are required to hold a Surf Rescue Certificate or Bronze Medallion. For information on swim requirements etc: Award prerequisites. If a family member is turning 13 by Sept. 30, they should gain their award at SRC/Bronze Week, a six-day intensive course just before Christmas. The course includes all meals and manual, and costs approximately $300.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Nipper Surf Sport parents should join as Supporters/General  members unless they hold a Bronze Medallion(if so, they are Associates). Nipper Surf Sport parents are required to have a Working With Children Check(WWCC) with OGSLSC listed on it.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Nipper Surf Ed parents are encouraged to become full members and fulfil WWCC requirements. Without WWCC, they are not allowed to access changerooms. They can join as Surf Ed Parent Social members without fulfilling WWCC requirements.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Full members are welcome to purchase a keyring fob ($20) or water proof wristband fob($25) for club access. Simply make the payment via your Members Area account, then fob will be programmed for you and we will email when ready to collect.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n